<div id="post-453516" class="blog-post position-5 odd-post"><div class="odd-post-inner blog-post-inner"><h1 class="title"><a href="http://softwarelivre.org/libreoffice/blog/libreoffice-infographics">LibreOffice Infographics</a></h1><span class="publishing-info"><span class="date">17 de Julho de 2012, 0:00</span><span class="author">, por Software Livre Brasil</span><span class="comments"> - <a href="/libreoffice/blog/libreoffice-infographics#comments_list"><span class='comment-count hide'>0</span><span class='comment-count-write-out'>sem comentários ainda</span></a></span></span><p><img class="alignnone" title="tdf-infographics1207.jpg" src="http://documentfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/tdf-infographics1207.jpg?w=900&amp;h=1431" border="0" height="1431" alt="LibreOffice Infographics July 2012" style="border: 0;" width="900"></p>
<p>If you are a LibreOffice user, you can download the Hybrid PDF from <a href="http://documentfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/tdf-infographics1207.pdf" title="LibreOffice Infographics July 2012">here</a> and open it as a normal ODF file (using File &gt; Open). If you are not a LibreOffice user, you can open the file using a PDF viewer, or install LibreOffice to discover this unique feature.</p>
